            "id": "4542797",
            "title": "Surf Air Mobility has big eVTOL plans in Hawaii",
            "description": "<html><body><p data-eci=\"true\">Surf Air Mobility (SFRM) announced a partnership with the Hawaii Department of Transportation and electric aerospace company BETA Technologies supporting their joint proposal for the Electric Vertical Takeoff and Landing Integration Pilot Program, which is a federal initiative under the White House's Advanced Air Mobility strategy. </p>\n<p>The company said the goal of the collaboration is to position Hawaii as a launch market for electric and advanced air mobility aircraft by leveraging Surf Air's (SFRM) operational network and BETA’s electric aircraft technology. Notably, Surf Air (SFRM) subsidiary Mokulele Airlines operates high-frequency interisland routes across nine destinations, providing a ready-made framework for integrating electrified aircraft into commercial service. The partnership plans to begin with cargo missions on existing Mokulele routes using BETA’s ALIA electric aircraft, designed for short-haul flights similar to Mokulele’s 51-mile average stage length.</p>\n<p>\"As Hawaii’s largest commuter airline flying approximately 100 flights daily, we understand the routes and operational realities,\" stated Surf Air Mobility (SFRM) CEO Deann White. \"Our infrastructure is perfectly suited to introduce next-generation aircraft. Participating in the eIPP initiative with BETA would support Hawaii’s leadership in advanced air mobility while delivering quieter, lower-emission transportation for communities and visitors,\" added White.</p>\n<p>Shares of Surf Air (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/SRFM\" title=\"Surf Air Mobility Inc.\">SRFM</a></span>) were up 2.3% in premarket trading on Tuesday.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
            "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/assets/og_image_1200-29b2bfe1a595477db6826bd2126c63ac2091efb7ec76347a8e7f81ba17e3de6c.png",
